    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese sculptors who specialize in creating Buddha statues. Their workshops were known as Bussho, and the sculptors had ranks ranging from shoubusshi (assistant) to daibusshi (master).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
